reviews.text: Beautiful place, worth visiting worth driving. Eden is like heaven. Is like no where else in the world. We went with Family and friends and we really enjoyed every step of the way. The view was spectacular. We walked all over Eden Park visiting Mirror Lake and all the Lookouts of the Ohio River . The sidewalks are in great shape and most of the walkers were very friendly. It's nice to get out and enjoy the sights .
I had a lovely time at this park. It seems very big so bring a bike. I like to play a game and this location was great for the game i play. #ingress

I love this place. For quiet hiking I wouldn't recommend. It can be heavy trafficked, esp during summer and spring. But gorgeous view of the river and Kentucky! Great fountain to walk around. Right by the conservatory and also right by Art Museum!!! Special place right in the heart of Cincinnati
Great place to run,  walk or just sit in your car and relax.  Nice park for the kids and some of the best views in the city.

If you are in town, I would suggest you visit here. A thrilling place to sit and watch people. It is a clean park full of people enjoying themselves and the surroundings. You will feel safe and relaxed. The neighborhood is great. It's a classic park. I highly recommend you to visit here on weekends.

This is a great place to have a celebration, gatherings or meetings. This place is wonderful. You can sit indoors or outdoors overlooking the marina on a warm sunset night. Great atmosphere! Great service... Sunday champagne brunch was amazing. Great variety of food and good selection on the menu. The management staff caters to your needs. Vallet parking is $5.00. I love this place.

We ate simple here with a club sandwich and a kids quesadilla. Both were well prepared and served quickly. 

Their patio seating in back has a marina view but no foot traffic by the tables. In front they have a coy pond with some hungry fish.

I go salsa dancing here and they're really great! Very fun and active, nice atmosphere. Havent tried the food as I go for more social dance experience but seems like a great place to eat both for friends and romantic scene. Glad they are still around.

Very attentive waiting staff was refilling drinks before being asked. Parking was valet only since I believe they were painting the parking spot numbers at the time. I had the roast beef dip sandwich and garlic mashed potatoes which was very tasty.

The restaurant is 3.5 stars for food & service, ambience is 5 stars for sure. 

OTOH, the bar on this Saturday night was off the charts for live music with the Rick Whitfield Band. Even the First Lady of Folk, Joni Mitchell, was in the house and the band played Woodstock in tribute. Very cool!

We had great service. Food and beverage was  excellent-presentation, amount, the way it is cooked. The whole event was catered well, no problem with the cleanliness of the toilets. We had a wonderful night.

As a regular visitor to Darwin, I have stayed in lots of hotels throughout town. But, I have now found THE ONE. This is hands down 100% credited to the absolutely immaculate condition of the lagoon pool! The beach is amazing and I have never seen any pool water so crystal clear, I was completely dumbfounded. The rooms were great too, no doubt about it. But, I will return here every time I come back mainly for the pool, it is MAGNETIC, cant stay away from it!

Sky city currently have a deal for locals. It is highly recommended. It also includes $100 to spend on drinks or in any of the Sky city reataurants. Unfortunately, the deal does not include the new wing of the complex called the Resort. It is such a great opportunity to get away without leaving Darwin. We would definitely come back again!

Loved the hotel and venue but your double standards disgusted me.  I booked a suite and showed up wearing a veterans motorcycle club t shirt, no problems at check in and you took my 500+ easy, but when I tried to exit hotel and enter casino apparently my t-shirt is not acceptable.. We are not an outlawed club and if it wasn't for veterans having once served you would not have the privilege of building a casino where you have
Casino Pretty good. Very relaxed atmosphere. Resort great clean great when you want a weekend get away and gamble.
